abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Virginia presents the first high-stakes trial of Democrats’ zero-tolerance policy, and a look at how Republicans may weaponize those politics.

abstract: House Democrats introduced a resolution calling for a sweeping environmental and economic mobilization that would make the United States carbon neutral by 2030.
snippet: House Democrats introduced a resolution calling for a sweeping environmental and economic mobilization that would make the United States carbon neutral by 2030.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Liberal Democrats put flesh on their “Green New Deal” slogan on Thursday with a sweeping resolution intended to redefine the national debate on climate change by calling for the United States to eliminate additional emissions of carbon by 2030.

abstract: Allegations of racism that have besieged Democrats have spread to a G.O.P. lawmaker, who helped oversee a college yearbook with racist photographs and slurs.
snippet: Allegations of racism that have besieged Democrats have spread to a G.O.P. lawmaker, who helped oversee a college yearbook with racist photographs and slurs.
lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — The political tumult in Virginia widened Thursday as the State Senate’s top Republican faced an onslaught of questions about racist photographs and slurs in a college yearbook that he helped oversee, transforming the Capitol’s nearly week-old crisis into a bipartisan reckoning over personal conduct.

headline_main: Trump Delivered Address. Democratic Women Sent a Message Too.

abstract: The State of the Union address suggested that America’s political drama was becoming an ensemble, not a one-man show anymore.
snippet: The State of the Union address suggested that America’s political drama was becoming an ensemble, not a one-man show anymore.
lead_paragraph: In 2011, Donald J. Trump, host of “The Celebrity Apprentice,” was the star of a Comedy Central roast, a familiar ritual for showbiz personae. The guest of honor sits stage center and gets insulted, then everyone laughs it off as all in good fun.

headline_main: Trump, Political TV’s Protagonist, Now Has to Share the Spotlight
headline_print_headline: No Longer the Center of Attention

abstract: After she delivered the Democratic response to the State of the Union address, some admirers asked why the clamoring has been louder for some white men to run than for her.
snippet: After she delivered the Democratic response to the State of the Union address, some admirers asked why the clamoring has been louder for some white men to run than for her.
lead_paragraph: Seconds into the Democratic response to President Trump’s State of the Union address Tuesday evening, speculation took off about the political future of Stacey Abrams, the Georgia leader who was delivering the remarks on behalf of her party.

abstract: Delivering her party’s rebuttal to the State of the Union speech, Ms. Abrams, who nearly became Georgia’s governor, said voter suppression was a threat to democracy.
snippet: Delivering her party’s rebuttal to the State of the Union speech, Ms. Abrams, who nearly became Georgia’s governor, said voter suppression was a threat to democracy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Stacey Abrams, who narrowly lost her race in November to be Georgia’s governor, delivered the Democrats’ official response to President Trump’s State of the Union address on Tuesday night by outlining the party’s vision for lower health care costs and a more inclusive immigration policy, and pressing her case that access to the voting booth should be easier, not harder.

abstract: As he has in past years, President Trump offered an unvarnished, unscripted view of the political world that went well beyond the heavily vetted speech he is to deliver to a joint session of Congress.
snippet: As he has in past years, President Trump offered an unvarnished, unscripted view of the political world that went well beyond the heavily vetted speech he is to deliver to a joint session of Congress.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For public consumption, President Trump planned to use his State of the Union address on Tuesday night to appeal for bipartisan unity. But at a private lunch for television anchors earlier in the day, he offered searing assessments of a host of Democrats.
